<br>
My current profile is:<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=233431">www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=233431</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
And as I have access to a GM elven smith, I'll probably fill up a few slots with more Blessed Mithril when I decide on cloak/belt for haste.<br>
<br>
Gaunts (to replace SCHW) are: 24 ac 5 dex 5 wis 25 hp/mana<br>
Belt is: 19 ac 5 cha 5 wis 40 hp/mana<br>
Cloak is: 16 ac 5 cha 10 wis 40 hp/mana<br>
<br>
About the only other thing worth noting is I'm currently about 5-10 weight over my encumberance limit, so the +10 str on the RBB is actually somewhat attractive.<br>
<br>
Ignoring for now relative availability, which would be the best to aim for (or any other suggestions, for that matter)?<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance.<br>
<br>
Caell Celedran<br>
54 paladin of Tunare<br>
Guild Leader, Wildrunners of Norrath<br>
Terris-Thule<br>
