 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhakashakamalakabalsaka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Haka Shakamalakabalsaka</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://hstrial-cman4.hssites.com/files/bootsmall.JPG" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 291<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/23/02 10:42:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1062.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hstrial-cman4.hssites.com/files/bootsmall.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Haste upgrade question</span><hr size=1> Upgrade your Sonic Wolf Earring and your Froglok Crown for starters is what I think...  There are a few helms such as the Helm of Raduken that have some Str on it.  A Sarnak Earring also has +5 str on it (from Chardok) but you can't buy those.<br>
<br>
Really, unless you're solo'ing, most groups will have some type of character that can cast a str buff, so you shouldn't be too bad until you upgrade further.  Maybe a tink bag would help?<br>
<br>
With regards to the haste item, dragon haste is a bit more expensive than the RBB, so it depends.  Also, the real only different between CoCw and CoF is the 50mana or 50hp.  Most people would rather have 50hp however they settle for the CoCw because they tend to be cheaper.  RBB's also have a bit lower haste so they're the cheapest of them all... the 5% haste different does make a different believe it or not.  If you have the cash to get a CoF then go for it, otherwise settle for a CoCW or an RBB.<br>
<br>
Edit:<br>
<br>
Actually, if you really have lots of cash or a guild that can help you out, consider getting an RBB and Lodi sheild to help you out with str issues. <p>Haka Shakamalakabalsaka <br>
